{"id":9365,"date":"2024-01-19T18:43:00","date_gmt":"2020-05-19T13:13:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=9365"},"modified":"2023-04-15T15:45:59","modified_gmt":"2023-04-15T10:15:59","slug":"green-bedroom-designs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/green-bedroom-designs\/","title":{"rendered":"Green Bedroom Designs That Will Make You Feel You\u2019re In The Lap Of Nature"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Energise, revitalise, and get in touch with nature! Surround yourself with green even if greenery comes in the form of <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/\"><em>interior design<\/em><\/a><em> elements.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether you&#8217;re looking to spice up your bedroom with colours and accessories or turning your bland space into a refreshing zone, the best advice we can give you is to go green. Even the tiniest splash of nature\u2019s dominant colour &#8211; green &#8211; can bring a lot of exuberance into your bedroom.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are countless ways to liven up your bedroom, a space that is so intimate and where you spend so much time. Green bedroom designs are popping everywhere on the internet and decor magazines. And if you are a nature enthusiast or an environmentally conscious person, green is the colour for you! From lime, forest, emerald or pastel &#8211; the myriad shades of green are endless. So let&#8217;s take a look at green bedroom design ideas worth noticing. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bottle Green Colour For The Bedroom<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The colour green exudes calmness and brings in a relaxed vibe to spaces. Green isn&#8217;t just for the garden, and when used right, it can make a mellow, gentle statement to any space. Bottle green paint in a bedroom will make it calm, invigorating, comforting and refreshing. This image shows how the colour green brings in a soothing vibe to this bedroom. And teamed up with a brown bed and closet it lends a modern look.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182356\/bottle-green-paint-colors-for-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Bottle green paint colors for bedrooms will make it calm, invigorating, comforting and refreshing.\" class=\"wp-image-9366\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182356\/bottle-green-paint-colors-for-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182356\/bottle-green-paint-colors-for-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182356\/bottle-green-paint-colors-for-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182356\/bottle-green-paint-colors-for-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Do not overpower the room with multiple colours, keep it simple and basic<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/green-room-paint-ideas\/\">Green Room Colours For Your Home<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Restful Retreat With Forest Green<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Forest green can work with big and small spaces alike. It looks magnificent even on walls. Dark green resonates with a deep jungle and can be paired with any neutral colour to bring out the essence of a bedroom. This colour has the power to change your mood instantaneously and make you feel fresh and energised in the mornings. Deep brown hardwood flooring and a creamy white wall with a few indoor plants makes this bedroom bloom with sophistication.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182409\/forest-green-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Forest green bedroom has the power to change your mood instantaneously and make you feel fresh and energised.\" class=\"wp-image-9367\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182409\/forest-green-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182409\/forest-green-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182409\/forest-green-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182409\/forest-green-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A dark wood floor or black accessories make this bedroom feel like a forest<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Embrace cosy ambient bedroom design for your home\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/15153502\/embrace-cosy-ambient-bedroom-design-for-your-home-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Zesty Lime Green Bedroom<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>On a deep primitive level, humans have always associated the colour green with fertility, wealth and safety. Paint all four walls in your bedroom with zesty lime green for an energising spark. It will make you feel calm yet joyful. You can tone the level of brightness of this shade in your bedroom with a few touches of light blue or white for a peaceful aura.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182717\/zesty-lime-green-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Zesty lime green bedroom makes you feel calm yet joyful with a few touches of light blue or white for a peaceful aura.\" class=\"wp-image-9375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182717\/zesty-lime-green-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182717\/zesty-lime-green-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182717\/zesty-lime-green-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182717\/zesty-lime-green-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Use lime green and combine it with a different shade such as white to bring it down a notch or two\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Pink And Green Bedroom<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Shades of green blend perfectly together, so don&#8217;t be afraid to mix light and dark. A pink and green bedroom scheme has a touch of softness. This pairing here as shown in this image portrays a sense of calmness to this space. As a combination it can go well with any style contemporary to rustic. Team green with pink to keep the effect crisp and clean. Natural wooden furniture is ideal to bring in warmth to this mix. Make sure to add a bit of white and grey to break up the monotony of both colours.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182611\/pink-and-green-bedroom.jpg\" alt=\"Pink and green bedroom colors combination it can go well with any style contemporary to rustic.\" class=\"wp-image-9373\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182611\/pink-and-green-bedroom.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182611\/pink-and-green-bedroom-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182611\/pink-and-green-bedroom-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182611\/pink-and-green-bedroom-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>The pink and green together is stunning and how the accent pieces are placed throughout the room\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Accessorise With Green Indoor Plants<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If your space isn&#8217;t blessed with ample square footage, that doesn&#8217;t mean you can&#8217;t have a bedroom that\u2019s abundant with the colour green. You don&#8217;t have to go shopping either to decor stores or spend a fortune. Accessorise your bedroom with beautiful indoor plants to give life to your bedroom and add this colour to your bedroom. Indoor plants add visual interest and also help purify the air regularly.  <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182546\/green-colour-bedroom-indoor-plants.jpg\" alt=\"Green bedroom with plants to give life and add visual interest and also help purify the air regularly.\" class=\"wp-image-9372\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182546\/green-colour-bedroom-indoor-plants.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182546\/green-colour-bedroom-indoor-plants-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182546\/green-colour-bedroom-indoor-plants-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182546\/green-colour-bedroom-indoor-plants-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Indoor plants take minimal space, and if you want a touch of green then, this is the best option  \n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/indoor-hanging-plants\/\">Indoor Hanging Plants For Your Home<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Welcome Tropics<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s take a trip to tropical land! If you want an easy and affordable solution to include green in your bedroom, wallpapers are a great choice. A tropical wallpapered wall, warm toned cushions and pillows, and a statement chandelier will cultivate a vacation flavour. The image shows how wallpaper is paired with natural wooden elements, tables, wooden flooring, and an indoor plant to enrich your bedroom interiors<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182707\/welcome-tropics-green-bedroom-colors.jpg\" alt=\"Tropical green bedroom wallpaper is an easy and affordable solution to include green in your bedroom.\" class=\"wp-image-9374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182707\/welcome-tropics-green-bedroom-colors.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182707\/welcome-tropics-green-bedroom-colors-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182707\/welcome-tropics-green-bedroom-colors-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182707\/welcome-tropics-green-bedroom-colors-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption> <em>Illuminate the look with placing table lamps on each side of the bed to feature the wall<\/em> <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read:&nbsp; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/wallpaper-designs-for-bedroom-walls\/\">Best Wallpaper Designs For Bedroom Walls<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Ahh So Dreamy! Beige And Green&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Another classic take on the colour green is to combine it with beige. They match perfectly without overlapping each other. In this bedroom, we can see only the bed and chairs offer beige accents but walls are covered in soft green. This decor enables you to quickly and relatively cheaply change it to another colour. Pink and beige accents can be used for a summer look, or charcoal and grey can be used if you want a sharper look in your bedroom.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182538\/green-bedroom-paint-and-beige-combo.jpg\" alt=\"Beige chairs and bed blends well with green colour bedroom and looks classic.\" class=\"wp-image-9371\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182538\/green-bedroom-paint-and-beige-combo.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182538\/green-bedroom-paint-and-beige-combo-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182538\/green-bedroom-paint-and-beige-combo-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182538\/green-bedroom-paint-and-beige-combo-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Play and experiment with different shades of colours that blend with green<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Make A Strong Statement With Green Furniture<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The less-is-more approach relies strongly on a particular piece of statement furniture &#8211; a bed, a bedside table or a chair, as it is in this case. A velvet green chair makes a grand statement in this bedroom and doesn&#8217;t overwhelm the entire space. An upholstered grey headboard works equally well with striped cushions and tropical patterned green bed sheet and pillows. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182512\/green-bedroom-furniture.jpg\" alt=\"Green bedroom furniture with gold and white stripes cleverly used to balance out all the green.\" class=\"wp-image-9370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182512\/green-bedroom-furniture.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182512\/green-bedroom-furniture-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182512\/green-bedroom-furniture-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182512\/green-bedroom-furniture-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>The use of gold and white stripes is cleverly used to balance out all the green\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Have you explored our wallpaper options for your master bedroom\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/09145250\/have-you-explored-our-wallpaper-options-for-your-master-bedroom.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Go Green With Curtains<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you do not want the four walls of your bedroom to be green yet you want to bring in this rather soothing and pleasant shade then give your windows a fair bit of thought. Whether you choose a light fabric or luxurious velvet, a green curtain is the best way to bring in shades of nature to your bedroom. In this image, we can see how the curtain panels are heavy but traditional. It complements the walls, and a blue rug brings in a pop of colour to the bedroom. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182416\/go-green-bedroom-curtains.jpg\" alt=\"Go green bedroom curtains are the best way to bring in soothing and pleasant shades of nature.\" class=\"wp-image-9368\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182416\/go-green-bedroom-curtains.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182416\/go-green-bedroom-curtains-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182416\/go-green-bedroom-curtains-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/19182416\/go-green-bedroom-curtains-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Cool blue accessories work smoothly against a green canvas for a tranquil space to sleep<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are numerous things you can do with the colour green in your bedroom. Try to be creative and experiment with different shades, mix and match until you are satisfied with the end result. If you have any suggestions or ideas, please feel free to write it down in the comments section below.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also Read:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/bedroom-paint-colours\/\">10 Best Bedroom Paint Colour Options<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/bedroom-design\/\">Best Bedroom Interior Designs From Design Cafe<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Unwind In Your Personal Sanctuary<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with modular interiors<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-pho